An international summit hosted by Indonesia will address the earthquake and tsunami aftermath, with 23 countries and major organizations invited.
Japan has deployed troops for rescue efforts in Indonesia, where the death toll has risen to 94,200.
Uzbekistan and China have sent humanitarian aid, while Australia pledges 1 billion Australian dollars in assistance.
Japan commits to long-term reconstruction projects in Aceh and North Sumatra.
The United Nations World Food Program is providing aid to Sumatra, Sri Lanka, and Indonesia.
Bangladesh is also sending relief goods to the tsunami victims.
The global response aims to support the affected regions in their recovery efforts.
